name: Air Canada 787-8 Dreamliner [C-GHPQ] Landing at Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
Follow me on Flickr: https://www.flickr.com/photos/dude8472productions/

Today, January 28th, 2016, Air Canada flew their first international 787 Dreamliner flight to Calgary Airport. The aircraft, C-GHPQ (the first 787 to ever visit YYC, in 2014), operated AC851 from London-Heathrow and touched down on runway 35R at 1515 local time. All of Air Canada's long haul flights from Calgary will be operated by 787s at the beginning of May. Enjoy this quick Dreamliner video!

Thanks for watching! Please comment, rate, and subscribe!
